{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "version": "2025-10-31T14:15:00-05:00",
  "description": "Meat yield curve for meat goat – Kiko. Aligned with Suka Smart Assistant’s cross-domain flow so you can: (1) plan/purchase goats, (2) butcher, (3) push to storehouse/inventory with grocery-section inspiration, (4) auto-suggest meal plans that match African/Middle Eastern/Caribbean goat dishes, (5) nudge the garden planner for peppers, tomatoes, okra, greens, (6) auto-generate cleaning/sanitation sessions, and (7) reverse-generate goating/butchery days from feast/storehouse/meal demands. User favorites/schedules are expected to be saved in Dexie/local DB; this file provides system defaults only.",
  "__notes": [
    "Kiko is a hardy meat goat, good fit for warm/wet climates — this ties back to your relocation/business plans (Northwestern Nigeria/Burkina Faso), so this profile should be available in the same yieldCurves folder as your sheep and cattle.",
    "This structure matches your other meat JSONs (Brangus, Senepol, Dexter, Katahdin, Dorper) so ImportService.js and ImportSettings.jsx can treat all yield curves uniformly.",
    "Reverse generation is especially powerful with goat because goat is often cooked in batches (pepper soup, curry, jollof meat, stew) → we can go from ‘I want 3 goat stews for next month’ to ‘You need 1 Kiko at 80–90 lb live, butcher on this date, clean with this profile, and tell the garden to grow or harvest peppers/onions.’"
  ],
  "animal": {
    "species": "goat",
    "breed": "Kiko",
    "class": "chevon/goat",
    "meat_goat": true,
    "typical_live_weight_lbs": [70, 85, 100, 120],
    "default_live_weight_lbs": 90,
    "live_to_hanging_yield_pct": 0.48,
    "hanging_to_carcass_yield_pct": 0.70,
    "default_hanging_days": 2,
    "butchery_style_default": "whole-or-primal-goat",
    "butchery_supported_styles": [
      "whole-or-primal-goat",
      "stew-heavy",
      "roast/BBQ",
      "halal/torah-compliant-no-unclean-cross-contamination"
    ],
    "torah_compliant_profile": {
      "allow_unclean_animals": false,
      "separate_tools_required": true,
      "separate_surfaces_required": true,
      "blood_draining_required": true,
      "notes": "Use goat-only knives/tables if the facility is processing other species; schedule goat-cleaning immediately after butchery."
    }
  },
